  "texts": [
    "However, unlike topic models, we represent topics in terms of complete sentences, rather than individual words.",
    "In doing so, we hope to capture more complex ideas contained in text than can be described with unordered lists of words.",
    "The method consists of three main stages.",
    "First, each document in the training data is cleaned and tokenised into individual sentences; each sentence is then represented in terms of a sentence embedding, i.e., a numerical feature vector.",
    "In the second stage, all sentences in the training data are fed into a clustering algorithm operating on sentence embeddings to create topical clusters of sentences."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}